events.name: San Jose State Spartans at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Trent Richardson ran for two touchdowns and Greg McElroy passed for 218 yards to help No. 1 Alabama beat San Jose State 48-3 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Top-ranked Alabama tramples San Jose State

events.name: Miami (OH) RedHawks at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Jeff Demps had a long scoring run, John Brantley added a fluky touchdown pass late and No. 4 Florida overcame an error-filled game to beat Miami (Ohio) 34-12 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida sloppy in win

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Rice Owls

headlines.description: Tre' Newton ran for three touchdowns, quarterback Garrett Gilbert was up and down in his first college start and No. 5 Texas overcame a slow start to beat Rice 34-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Horns overcome shaky Gilbert

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Andy Dalton ran for two touchdowns and threw for another score to make up for his two interceptions and No. 6 TCU opened the season with a 30-21 victory over No. 24 Oregon State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dalton's legs overcome INTs, lift TCU

events.name: Utah State Aggies at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: DeMarco Murray ran for 218 yards and two touchdowns and converted a key fourth down, helping No. 7 Oklahoma survived an unexpected scare from Utah State for a 31-24 victory on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Sooners survive Utah State on late pick

events.name: Western Kentucky Hilltoppers at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Looks like Nebraska found itself a quarterback, and he may be leading the Huskers for quite a while.
headlines.shortLinkText: Frosh Martinez stars in Nebraska rout

events.name: Eastern Illinois Panthers at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Adam Robinson ran for 109 yards and three touchdowns in the first half and No. 9 Iowa breezed past Eastern Illinois 37-7
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa blows past E. Illinois

events.name: New Mexico Lobos at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Kenjon Barner replaced suspended running back LaMichael James for No. 11 Oregon and ran for a career-high 147 yards and four touchdowns before catching another score in the Ducks' 72-0 season-opening rout of New Mexico on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barner's 5 TDs lift Ducks

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at UNLV Rebels

headlines.description: John Clay and Montee Ball each ran for two touchdowns to lead No. 12 Wisconsin past UNLV 41-21 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clay-Ball duo steadies Badgers past mistakes

events.name: South Carolina State Bulldogs at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Quarterback Joshua Nesbitt ran for 130 yards and three touchdowns, Roddy Jones added two scoring runs and No. 16 Georgia Tech beat South Carolina State 41-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nesbitt, No. 16 Georgia Tech drop S.C. State

events.name: Tennessee Tech Golden Eagles at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Ryan Mallett went 21 of 24 for 301 yards and three touchdowns to lead No. 17 Arkansas to a 44-3 victory over Tennessee Tech on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mallett slings 3 TDs as No. 17 Arkansas cruises

events.name: LSU Tigers at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Against all odds, undermanned North Carolina nearly rallied from a 20-point halftime deficit before losing 30-24 to LSU on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Depleted UNC falls short against LSU

events.name: Youngstown State Penguins at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: True freshman Rob Bolden threw for 239 yards and two touchdowns, Chaz Powell had a 100-yard kickoff return for a score and No. 19 Penn State brushed off a sluggish start Saturday to beat Youngstown State 44-14.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn St. rolls Youngstown St. after slow start

events.name: Samford Bulldogs at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Christian Ponder threw four first-half touchdown passes and Greg Reid returned a punt 74 yards for another score as No. 20 Florida State celebrated Jimbo Fisher's coaching debut with a 59-6 victory over lower-division Samford (Ala.) Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 20 FSU routs Samford in Fisher's debut

events.name: Arkansas State Red Wolves at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Making his first start, quarterback Cam Newton ran for 171 yards and two touchdowns and passed for 186 yards and three more scores to help Auburn beat overmatched Arkansas State 52-26 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Newton's 5 TDs in first start key No. 22 Auburn

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray passed for three touchdowns and ran for another in leading No. 23 Georgia to a 55-7 victory over Louisiana-Lafayette.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray lifts No. 23 UGA

events.name: Coastal Carolina Chanticleers at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw two touchdown passes and Noel Devine rushed for 111 yards and a score, leading No. 25 West Virginia to a 31-0 win over Coastal Carolina on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 25 West Virginia stifles Coastal Carolina

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Freshman Le'Veon Bell rushed for 141 yards on 10 carries and scored two touchdowns to spark Michigan State past Western Michigan 38-14 in a season-opening game Saturday.

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Missouri Tigers

headlines.shortLinkText: Mizzou uses second-half rally to hold off Illinois

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Derrick Locke ran for two touchdowns and Kentucky held off rival Louisville 23-16 Saturday, keeping the Governor's Cup for the fourth straight season and making Joker Phillips victorious in a matchup of longtime friends debuting as head coaches.

events.name: Jacksonville State Gamecocks at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Jacksonville State quarterback Coty Blanchard completed a 2-point conversion pass to Calvin Middleton in double overtime as the Gamecocks pulled off a stunning 49-48 victory over Mississippi on Saturday.

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Andre Ellington and Jamie Harper each scored twice for Clemson in a 35-10 victory over North Texas on Saturday that showed there's life for the Tigers without ACC player of the year C.J. Spiller.

events.name: UC Davis Aggies at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Kevin Riley threw for 258 yards and three touchdowns in just more than a half of work, Jeff Tedford became California's winningest coach in the modern era and the Golden Bears beat UC Davis 52-3 on Saturday for a sixth win their last seven season openers.
